HEADWORD: ronin
<hw>ro"nin"</hw> <pr>(r⟦omac⟧"n⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Jap. <ets>r⟦omac⟧-nin</ets>, fr. Chin. <ets>lang</ets> profligate,
lawless + <ets>j⟦ecir⟧n</ets> (old sound <ets>n⟦imac⟧n</ets>)
man.]</ety> <def>In Japan, under the feudal system, a samurai who had
renounced his clan or who had been discharged or ostracized and had
become a wanderer without a lord; an outcast; an outlaw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

